text: The 2027 New South Wales state election will be held no earlier than 30 January 2027 and no later than 27 March 2027 to elect the 59th Parliament of New South Wales, including all 93 seats in the Legislative Assembly and 21 of the 42 seats in the Legislative Council. It will be conducted by the New South Wales Electoral Commission (NSWEC). The incumbent Labor minority government, led by Premier Chris Minns, will try and win a second consecutive term in government, opposed by the Liberal/National Coalition, led by Opposition Leader Mark Speakman. ==References== Category:Elections in New South Wales Category:2027 Category:Future elections Category:2020s in New South Wales
title: 2027 New South Wales state election
